	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Ran a controlled test today with the Mind Crystal in Qeynos. The Mind Crystal grew warm when I put the Hasty Note in these locations:<br />
 <br />
No note (on alt) - yes<br />
Note on cursor - no<br />
Note on top inventory - no<br />
Note in bag - no<br />
Note in bank, top level - no<br />
Note in bank, in bag - no<br />
Note in shared bank - yes<br />
 <br />
Conclusion... the new "quest item checker" is capable of knowing whether you do (or don't) have a specific quest item regardless of whether that item is on your toon (in bags or not) or in your bank (in bags or not, but not shared bank). It probably uses the same logic as the Lore Item checker. <br />
 <br />
Which means if the Coven spawner is looking for your Hasty Note, it can be in your bank, in your bags, etc and the spawner will still see it.<br />
 <br />
It also means if the Coven spawner is looking for you NOT to have previous crystals, then they are not safe in your bags, in the bank, etc.<br />
 <br />
On a second note, I watched 5 druids come into SK, spawn the Coven on their first night, and leave successfully. I watched 2 druids wipe to Coven, looted nothing, and it spawned the next night for them as well. I also sat there, by myself in the zone, for another 10-odd hours with no spawn at all. I'm becoming more convinced that having a previous crystal blocks your own personal spawn. If any druid is present in the zone with a note AND without any crystals, then it spawns. I'm not quite ready to destroy it yet, but I'll continue testing.<br />
 <br />
One difficulty being that if multiple druids are there, we don't know which druid spawned it. This complicates matters because you could be trying to test something, it spawns, and unknown to you, the druid sitting behind you was the one actually responsible for it.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
